Where is Dean?

1153
01:18:05.760 --> 01:18:07.962
JACK: Behind you.

1154
01:18:07.962 --> 01:18:10.297
PHIL: I cannot thank you enough.

1155
01:18:10.297 --> 01:18:13.000
You kids really are
an inspiration to us all.

1156
01:18:13.000 --> 01:18:15.670
I mean that.
To Emma and to Dean.

1157
01:18:15.670 --> 01:18:17.539
ALL: To Emma and to Dean.

1158
01:18:17.539 --> 01:18:19.507
JACK: Hear, hear. Whoo!

1159
01:18:19.507 --> 01:18:21.643
Yeah.

1160
01:18:23.010 --> 01:18:24.946
[CHATTERING]

1161
01:18:24.946 --> 01:18:28.215
BARBARA: Thank you for coming.
JACK: Thanks for having us.

1162
01:18:28.215 --> 01:18:31.185
How come you're not over there
with everybody else?

1163
01:18:31.185 --> 01:18:34.689
I'm not really
an everybody-else kind of guy.

1164
01:18:34.689 --> 01:18:38.292
STACEY: Emma is. Always has been.

1165
01:18:38.292 --> 01:18:41.629
She's really good at that.
People really like her.

1166
01:18:41.629 --> 01:18:45.199
Yeah, I can see that.
Did you see any sharks?

1167
01:18:45.199 --> 01:18:48.803
It took her like two seconds
to become even more popular

1168
01:18:48.803 --> 01:18:50.471
than before you guys went away.

1169
01:18:50.471 --> 01:18:52.774
Yeah, I can see that too.

1170
01:18:52.774 --> 01:18:54.676
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1171
01:18:54.676 --> 01:18:57.912
[TIM HANAUER'S
"DECEMBER DAYS" PLAYING]

1172
01:19:00.347 --> 01:19:01.749
